---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Insights — needle-bench"
  description="Data-driven analysis of AI coding agents on real Docker bugs. 31 models, 40 benchmarks, 3 arms, 3,641 runs. Every claim cites specific numbers from the experiment."
>
  <main class="insights-hub">
    <section class="section">
      <h1>Insights</h1>
      <p>Analysis from 31 models &times; 40 benchmarks &times; 3 arms = 3,641 runs, 1,945 solved. Every claim cites specific data from <code>experiment-scores.json</code>. No marketing.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="articles">
        <a href="/insights/kernel-lift/" class="article-card">
          <h2>Kernel lift: what happens when the same model runs through a shared agent loop</h2>
          <p>Claude Opus goes from 58% native to 100% kernel. Grok-4-1-fast goes from 2.5% to 92.5%. The harness matters more than the model for a surprising share of the population.</p>
          <p class="meta">Kernel arm · 31 models</p>
        </a>

        <a href="/insights/open-source-coding-models/" class="article-card">
          <h2>Open-source coding models on real bugs</h2>
          <p>Kimi K2.5, Devstral, DeepSeek R1, Qwen3-Coder. How open-weight models perform head-to-head with closed frontier models when both sit inside the same agent loop.</p>
          <p class="meta">Open vs closed · kernel arm</p>
        </a>

        <a href="/insights/native-driver-vs-kernel/" class="article-card">
          <h2>Native driver vs kernel: does the CPU arm pay for itself?</h2>
          <p>The CPU arm wires the model straight into the ostk agent loop through a native API driver instead of OpenRouter. Sometimes the win is 2-3 points. Sometimes it's 57 points. We look at when the driver is worth building.</p>
          <p class="meta">Three-arm comparison · tested drivers</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section methodology">
      <h2>Methodology</h2>
      <p>Every insight article uses the same dataset: <code>public/experiment-scores.json</code>, built from the full 3-arm experiment run. Numbers are computed, not claimed. The leaderboard on the <a href="/">home page</a> shows the same data without commentary.</p>
      <p>Three arms per model, identical prompt, identical benchmark set:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Native</strong> &mdash; the vendor's own CLI (Claude Code, Gemini CLI, Codex, Vibe, Kimi CLI) or an OpenCode fallback.</li>
        <li><strong>Kernel</strong> &mdash; the ostk agent loop via OpenRouter, the controlled cross-vendor comparison.</li>
        <li><strong>CPU</strong> &mdash; the ostk agent loop via a native API driver (Anthropic, Google, OpenAI, Mistral).</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Scoring is deterministic: <code>test.sh</code> exits 0 on fix, 1 on fail. No LLM-as-judge, no subjective rubric.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  .insights-hub { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 1rem 1.5rem 3rem; }
  .insights-hub h1 { margin-top: 0; }
  .insights-hub .section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }

  .articles { display: grid; gap: 1rem; }
  .article-card {
    display: block; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px;
    text-decoration: none; color: inherit; transition: border-color 0.15s ease;
  }
  .article-card:hover { border-color: var(--text-muted); }
  .article-card h2 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.3; }
  .article-card p { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--text); }
  .article-card .meta { font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--text-muted); font-family: var(--mono); margin-bottom: 0; }

  .methodology h2 { font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
  .methodology p, .methodology li { font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.6; }
  .methodology ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem; }
</style>
